      <body>
         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">['Tonning ¶  28th. November 1852. ¶  ¶ How pleased we were over contents of letter sent through Dr. Sonder ¶ . You dear Bertha and my beloved Clara ¶ , and especially from you Bertha, and if we had no...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">52.11.28</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">Magdalene Mertens to Bertha and Clara Müller</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">Private hands.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-weight: bold; ">Corrected 3.12.91.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note>
               <note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Original letter not found. MS a typescript, 'Translated in Sydney from the German', found in Louise Wehl's scrapbook.</p>
               </note>['Tonning<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Tönning.</p>
               </note> 28th. November 1852.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>How pleased we were over contents of letter sent through Dr. Sonder<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">O. W. Sonder of Hamburg, Germany.</p>
               </note>. You dear Bertha and my beloved Clara<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bertha and Clara are still in Adelaide, while Ferdinand is in Melbourne or vicinity.</p>
               </note>, and especially from you Bertha, and if we had not received a line now and then from Ferdinand we would not have heard, and we are thankful that you are happy and well.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>And this is wonderful news for us if it will be the will of God that you should return one day how happy it would make us. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We still live here the same as usual happy and contented — and have the happiness to have children near. This happens to be Albertine. </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>And if you my beloved should return to our circle — How happy it would make us.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope you will get a good share of the gold<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Ferdinand had initially intended to join Eduard Wehl on the Victorian goldfields.</p>
               </note> and use it with joy towards your return.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Heavenly Father will give you what is best — Till then, in love</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Your Mother,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Magdaline<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.1665in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.1665in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Magdalene.</p>
               </note> Mertens.']</p>
         </div>
